Description: A concurrent, browser-impersonating scraper in Rust to download archived assets
 from the Internet Archive's Wayback Machine CDX API without being blocked.
 wayback is a concurrent, browser-impersonating scraper written in Rust that
 downloads archived assets from the Internet Archive's Wayback Machine CDX API
 without being blocked. It uses libcurl-impersonate to mimic real browser TLS
 fingerprints and HTTP headers, allowing it to bypass bot-detection mechanisms.

